sbol:Collection.ns1:abstract: Mathematical modeling of genetic circuits generally assumes that gene expression is at steady state when measurements are performed. However, conventional methods of measurement do not necessarily guarantee that this assumption is satisfied. In this study, we reveal a bi-plateau mode of gene expression at the single-cell level in bacterial batch cultures. The first plateau is dynamically active, where gene expression is at steady state; the second plateau, however, is dynamically inactive. We further demonstrate that the predictability of assembled genetic circuits in the first plateau (steady state) is much higher than that in the second plateau where conventional measurements are often performed. By taking the nature of steady state into consideration, our method of measurement promises to directly capture the intrinsic property of biological parts/circuits regardless of circuit–host or circuit–environment interactions.

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.ns1:title: PTac
sbol:SequenceAnnotation.ns1:description: Promoter regulated by the engineered repressor LacI (C1d or C63m) or its engineered variant LacI-M (C72m). Has low cross-talk when used with other members of the Marionette system when used with C72m. Constitutively active, and is repressed »500x by C1d, C63m, or C72m when the repressor is not complexed with Isopropyl-B-D-thiogalactiside (IPTG).
